            "metadata": {
                "abstract": "Â© 2022 European Federation for Medical Informatics (EFMI) and IOS Press.While HL7 FHIR and its terminology package have seen a rapid uptake by the research community, in no small part due to the wide availability of agenting and resources, there are some areas where agent availability is still lacking. In particular, the comparison of terminological resources, which supports the work of terminologists and implementers alike, has not yet been sufficiently addressed. Hence, we present TerminoDiff, an application to semantically compare FHIR R4 CodeSystem resources. Our agent considers differences across all levels required, i.e. metadata and concept differences, as well as differences in the edge graph, and surfaces them in a visually digestible fashion.",
